        <name>
            <text>Umkehrfunktion (3)</text>
        </name>
        <questiontext format="html">
            <text><![CDATA[
[[lang code="de"]]Die Gleichung der Umkehrfunktion zu \(f(x)= \sqrt{3 \cdot x +1}\) lautet:[[/lang]][[lang code="en"]]The equation of the reversal function \(f(x)= \sqrt{3 \cdot x +1}\) reads:[[/lang]]
]]></text>
        </questiontext>
        <generalfeedback format="html">
            <text><![CDATA[
[[lang code="de"]]
<p>
    <strong>
        L&#246;sungsweg:
    </strong>
</p>
<p>
    L&#246;se \(y= \sqrt{3 \cdot x +1}\) nach \(x\) auf:
    <br/>
</p>
<p>
    <span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">
        \(y= \sqrt{3\cdot x +1}\)&#160; \(| \big(\ldots\big)^2\)
    </span>
    <br/>
</p>
<p>
    \(\Rightarrow\)&#160; \(y^2=3 \cdot x+1\)&#160; \(| -1\)
</p>
<p>
    \(\Leftrightarrow\)&#160; \(y^2-1=3 \cdot x\)&#160; \(| :3\)
    <br/>
</p>
<p>
    \(\Leftrightarrow\)&#160; \(\dfrac{y^2-1}{3}=x\)
</p>
<p>
    Das hei&#223;t \(f^{-1}(x)=\dfrac{x^2-1}{3}\).
</p>
[[/lang]][[lang code="en"]]
<p>
    <strong>
        Solution:
    </strong>
</p>
<p>
    Sold \(y= \sqrt{3 \cdot x +1}\) After \(x\) on:
    <br/>
</p>
<p>
    <span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">
        \(y= \sqrt{3\cdot x +1}\) \(| \big(\ldots\big)^2\)
    </span>
    <br/>
</p>
<p>
    \(\Rightarrow\) \(y^2=3 \cdot x+1\) \(| -1\)
</p>
<p>
    \(\Leftrightarrow\) \(y^2-1=3 \cdot x\) \(| :3\)
    <br/>
</p>
<p>
    \(\Leftrightarrow\) \(\dfrac{y^2-1}{3}=x\)
</p>
<p>
    That means \(f^{-1}(x)=\dfrac{x^2-1}{3}\).
</p>
[[/lang]]
]]></text>
